fix: directory-aware schema format detection for lint, breaking, semver

Add intelligent format detection that works on directories in addition to
files. When no explicit format is provided, the commands now:

1. Walk the directory tree to find the first schema file with a recognized
   extension (.proto, .avsc, .parquet, etc.)
2. Fall back to DetectFormatFromModuleRoots() which infers format from the
   configured module_roots (e.g., "internal/apis/proto" → proto)

This eliminates the need to specify --format when running `apx lint`,
`apx breaking`, and `apx semver suggest` from a directory root.

Added DetectFormatFromModuleRoots() to infer schema format from module_roots
configuration. Added detectFormatFromDir() to walk directories and find the
first schema file. Updated DetectFormat() to handle both files and directories.

New tests cover:
- Directory walking with various schema file types
- Module roots with single and multiple roots
- Mixed format roots (unsupported)
- Format aliases (protobuf, swagger)

All 23 format detection tests pass. Full test suite: 16 packages, all passing.
